  "parent": "pt-BR",
  "notes": "Baiano (Salvador and Bahia). Northeastern-type open pretonic vowels /e/ -> [ɛ], /o/ -> [ɔ]. RESOLVED contradiction (prior notes said 'no /t,d/ palatalisation', but the inventory carried [t͡ʃ,d͡ʒ]): the two ALiB phenomena are distinct — Salvador DOES palatalise /t,d/ before /i/ ('africadas baianas', following the broad Brazilian pattern), and only the separate post-glide context (muito, oito) shows low rates. Palatalisation before /i/ is therefore RETAINED. Coda /S/ stays ALVEOLAR [s,z] in Salvador and the Bahian interior (NOT the Recife/Carioca chiado). Some /ʎ/ -> [j] weakening (allophones). Afro-Brazilian prosodic substratum.",
  "quality": "research",
  "script_type": "alphabet",
